Blofeld Installation
====================

Dependencies
------------

Before installing Blofeld, you need to have these libraries and applications:

 * Python 2.5 or newer
   http://python.org

 * CherryPy 3 
   http://www.cherrypy.org

 * Cheetah
   http://www.cheetahtemplate.org

 * Python Imaging Library
   http://www.pythonware.com/products/pil/

 * Mutagen 1.17 or newer
   http://code.google.com/p/mutagen/

 * Couchdbkit
   http://couchdbkit.org

 * GStreamer with Python bindings
   http://gstreamer.freedesktop.org
   http://gstreamer.freedesktop.org/modules/gst-python.html

 * CouchDB
   http://couchdb.apache.org


Installation
------------

After installing the dependencies, you can install Blofeld by running:

  sudo python setup.py install

This will automatically install all required Python modules. To start Blofeld
now you can use:

  blofeld

Once Blofeld is running, point your web browser to http://localhost:8083/ to
access the web interface.


Running From the Source Tree
----------------------------

If you want to run Blofeld from the source directory without installing, you
just need to run:

  python Blofeld.py

